main event: Observers watched three objects in the sky for several hours and thirty minutes, moving in a triangular and square pattern.
interesting points: The objects emitted a rattling, humming, buzzing sound,The main body of light was flashing and changing colors,The objects moved across the sky from south to northeast,The objects had an apparent size of 25-30 feet,The sighting was reported to Suffolk County Strategic Air Command on 2-6-1966.
witness description: A 19-year-old male and his 17-year-old wife, along with his father and mother
